Telkom Kenya has introduced new volume-based data offers with a wider validity period at a browsing rate of nine cents per MB.The new improvements include 24-hour and 48-hour data expiry notification, improved navigation tools to view data offers, ease of USSD purchase via the universal *544#, and data bundle extensions before the expiry of a current data offer. Telkom Kenya seeks to provide value to our customers through our service and offerings, chief corporate communications officer George Mlaghui said.The Communications Authority of Kenya statistics report for the first quarter of the financial year 2015-16 shows data subscription at 24.8 million from 23.9 million reported in the same period the previous year.Internet users grew by 1.9 million from 35.5 million.